benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC18, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC26 cover successful resume operations with required headers and parameters.
Empty Response: @TC05 covers the case when no bundle exists, returning 404.
Non-Existing Resource: @TC05 covers attempting to resume a non-existent bundle.
Invalid bundleId format: @TC06 tests invalid UUID format resulting in 400.
Missing headers: @TC07 tests missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header resulting in 400.
Already active or cancelled bundle: @TC08 and @TC09 cover invalid state errors.
Unauthorized access: @TC10 covers invalid token/user resulting in 401/403.
Extra/unexpected parameters: @TC11 tests ignoring or handling extra query params.
Maximum length headers and parameters: @TC12 covers boundary testing for header and header length.
Large number of pluginProperty values: @TC13 tests handling of many plugin properties and limits.
System errors: @TC14 covers internal server errors when dependencies are unavailable.
Retry mechanism: @TC15 covers transient network failures and retries.
Security tests: @TC16 and @TC17 cover injection and XSS attempts.
Partial input: @TC18 tests minimal required fields.
Invalid parameter format: @TC19 tests wrong format for pluginProperty.
RequestedDate in past: @TC20 covers invalid date handling.
Concurrent requests: @TC21 tests race conditions and multiple simultaneous requests.
Performance: @TC22 covers load testing under normal and peak conditions.
Regression: @TC23 covers previously fixed edge cases.
Backward compatibility: @TC24 tests legacy header formats.
Degraded plugin service: @TC25 tests high latency or timeout scenarios.
Whitespace and case variations in headers: @TC26 tests header normalization.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate rate limiting or throttling scenarios.
Authorization: No explicit tests for token refresh or detailed permission checks beyond invalid user.
Edge cases for pluginProperty: No tests for malformed or unexpected data types beyond non-array input.
Timeouts and network failures beyond transient retries: No explicit tests for prolonged timeouts or network partition scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling when retrieving or listing bundles.
Include scenarios verifying caching headers and cache invalidation.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Expand authorization tests to include permission levels and token refresh scenarios.
Test malformed pluginProperty inputs, such as non-array types or invalid strings.
Simulate prolonged network failures or timeouts to verify system resilience and timeout handling.
